/* Now, This is the NOT clause practice query,The NOT clause is used to exclude certain records from the result 
 set based on specified conditions.*/ 
 SELECT
   Product_Name
 FROM
  superstore.superstore_sales_data
  WHERE
   NOT Category = 'FURNITURE';
   /* This query will return a list of product names from the superstore_sales_data table where the category is not 'FURNITURE'. 
   The NOT operator is used to exclude all records that belong to the 'FURNITURE' category, 
   allowing us to focus on products from other categories. */


   -- Now, this is NOT and ORDER BY to sort the data in descending order 
   SELECT 
    Customer_Name, Sales, Product_Name
    FROM 
     superstore.superstore_sales_data
     WHERE
      NOT Product_Name = 'Samsung Galaxy' AND NOT State = 'California'
      ORDER BY Sales DESC;
/* This query retrieves the customer name, sales amount, and product name from the superstore_sales_data table, 
excluding records where the product name is 'Samsung Galaxy' and the state is 'California'. 
The NOT operator is used to filter out these specific conditions, and the ORDER BY clause sorts the resulting data 
in descending order based on the sales amount, allowing us to see the highest sales figures at the top of the result set. */ 